cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the implementation of synchronous systems in a distributed and asynchronous manner, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
2. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper deals with the causal structure of system behavior, which is a topic of interest in logic and formal methods. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the implementation of a system, which is a topic of interest in programming languages. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the behavior of a system and its implementation, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve the use of data structures and algorithms in the implementation of the system, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
